# MINI_SOC_VERIFICATION_PLAN_v1.0

## 1. Introduction

### Purpose

This document defines the verification strategy and verification objectives for the Mini SoC.

The purpose of verification is to ensure:

* Functional correctness
* Register correctness
* Bus protocol compliance
* Interrupt functionality
* Error handling
* SoC integration correctness

---

# 2. Verification Scope

The following blocks are included in verification scope.

| Block               | Verification Scope |
| ------------------- | ------------------ |
| GPIO                | Included           |
| TIMER               | Included           |
| DMA                 | Included           |
| APB Interface       | Included           |
| AXI-Lite Interface  | Included           |
| APB Address Decoder | Included           |
| AXI-to-APB Bridge   | Included           |
| Interrupt Logic     | Included           |

---

# 3. Verification Methodology

Verification shall be performed using SystemVerilog.

The environment shall contain:

* Driver/BFM
* Monitor
* Scoreboard
* Assertions
* Functional Coverage

Verification shall proceed in phases:

Phase-1

```
RTL + Directed Tests
```

Phase-2

```
Monitor + Scoreboard
```

Phase-3

```
Functional Coverage
```

Phase-4

```
Assertions
```

Phase-5

```
Full SoC Integration
```

---

# 4. Reset Verification

## Objective

Verify correct behavior after reset.

### Features

Verify:

* All registers reset correctly
* Interrupts deasserted
* DMA enters IDLE state
* APB interface returns default values

### Success Criteria

All reset values match RAS specification.

---

# 5. GPIO Verification

## Feature: GPIO Enable

### Objective

Verify GPIO enable control.

### Checks

* Enable bit writable
* Disable bit writable
* Readback correct

---

## Feature: GPIO Direction

### Objective

Verify direction configuration.

### Checks

* All direction bits programmable
* Readback correct

---

## Feature: GPIO Data Output

### Objective

Verify output data register.

### Checks

* Write operation
* Readback operation
* Output pin update

---

## Feature: GPIO Data Input

### Objective

Verify input data register.

### Checks

* External pin changes reflected
* Register updates correctly

---

## Feature: GPIO Interrupt

### Objective

Verify interrupt generation.

### Checks

* Status bit set
* Interrupt asserted
* Interrupt cleared via RW1C

---

# 6. TIMER Verification

## Feature: Timer Enable

### Objective

Verify timer start operation.

### Checks

* Counter starts decrementing
* Counter stops when disabled

---

## Feature: Timer Countdown

### Objective

Verify countdown operation.

### Checks

* Count decrements each cycle
* No skipped counts

---

## Feature: One-Shot Mode

### Objective

Verify single timeout generation.

### Checks

* Timeout asserted once
* Counter stops

---

## Feature: Periodic Mode

### Objective

Verify automatic reload.

### Checks

* Reload occurs
* Multiple timeout events occur

---

## Feature: Timer Interrupt

### Objective

Verify timeout interrupt.

### Checks

* Timeout bit set
* Interrupt asserted
* Interrupt clear operation

---

# 7. DMA Verification

## Feature: DMA Start

### Objective

Verify DMA start command.

### Checks

* Start bit accepted
* State changes to BUSY

---

## Feature: DMA Busy State

### Objective

Verify BUSY indication.

### Checks

* Busy bit asserted
* Busy bit cleared after completion

---

## Feature: DMA Completion

### Objective

Verify DONE state.

### Checks

* DONE bit asserted
* Interrupt generated

---

## Feature: DMA Error

### Objective

Verify ERROR state.

### Checks

* Error bit asserted
* Error bit cleared through RW1C

---

# 8. APB Protocol Verification

## Feature: APB Write

### Objective

Verify APB write transactions.

### Checks

* Correct address phase
* Correct enable phase
* Register updated

---

## Feature: APB Read

### Objective

Verify APB read transactions.

### Checks

* Correct address phase
* Correct data return

---

## Feature: Back-to-Back Transactions

### Objective

Verify sequential accesses.

### Checks

* No data corruption
* Correct responses

---

## Feature: Invalid Address

### Objective

Verify illegal access handling.

### Checks

* PSLVERR asserted
* No register corruption

---

# 9. Address Decoder Verification

## Feature: GPIO Decode

### Objective

Verify GPIO address selection.

### Checks

* GPIO selected only for valid addresses

---

## Feature: TIMER Decode

### Objective

Verify TIMER address selection.

### Checks

* TIMER selected only for valid addresses

---

## Feature: DMA Decode

### Objective

Verify DMA address selection.

### Checks

* DMA selected only for valid addresses

---

## Feature: Invalid Decode

### Objective

Verify invalid region handling.

### Checks

* No slave selected
* Error response generated

---

# 10. AXI-Lite Verification

## Feature: AXI Write Channel

### Objective

Verify write transactions.

### Checks

* AW channel handshake
* W channel handshake
* B response generation

---

## Feature: AXI Read Channel

### Objective

Verify read transactions.

### Checks

* AR channel handshake
* R channel handshake

---

## Feature: Error Response

### Objective

Verify invalid address response.

### Checks

* SLVERR response returned

---

# 11. AXI-to-APB Bridge Verification

## Objective

Verify protocol conversion.

### Checks

AXI Write

```
Generates APB write
```

AXI Read

```
Generates APB read
```

Address

```
Preserved correctly
```

Data

```
Preserved correctly
```

Errors

```
Propagated correctly
```

---

# 12. Interrupt Verification

## Objective

Verify all interrupt sources.

### Features

GPIO Interrupt

TIMER Interrupt

DMA Interrupt

### Checks

* Assertion
* Deassertion
* Masking
* Clearing

---

# 13. Scoreboard Requirements

Scoreboard shall verify:

GPIO

* Control registers
* Direction registers
* Status registers

TIMER

* Control registers
* Countdown values
* Timeout status

DMA

* Configuration registers
* State transitions
* Status values

---

# 14. Assertion Requirements

Assertions shall verify:

APB Protocol

* PENABLE only after PSEL
* Stable address during transfer

AXI-Lite Protocol

* Valid/Ready handshakes

Register Rules

* RO registers not modified
* RW1C behavior correct

---

# 15. Coverage Goals

Coverage target:

```
>95%
```

Coverage categories:

* Register accesses
* Interrupts
* APB transactions
* AXI transactions
* Error responses
* State transitions

---

# 16. Exit Criteria

Verification shall be considered complete when:

* All planned tests pass
* No open functional bugs
* Coverage goal achieved
* Assertions pass
* Scoreboard clean
* No protocol violations observed

End of Document
